<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>ScrollTax Reset Plan</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #0f172a;
      color: white;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 40px;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 900px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 52px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 28px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    p, li {
      line-height: 1.7;
      font-size: 18px;
    }

    .muted {
      color: #94a3b8;
    }

    .card {
      background: #020617;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 24px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .warning {
      color: #f87171;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .highlight {
      color: #fbbf24;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .button {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #22c55e;
      color: white;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 14px 22px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .button:hover {
      opacity: 0.95;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    .small {
      color: #64748b;
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }

    .price-box {
      background: #111827;
      border: 1px solid #1f2937;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 24px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .price {
      font-size: 38px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin: 10px 0;
    }

    .section-space {
      margin-top: 50px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Break the Scroll Habit in 7 Days</h1>
    <p class="muted">You do not need more motivation. You need a system that stops the loop.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <p class="warning">If you keep scrolling like this, the cost is not just time.</p>
      <p>It is money. Focus. Sleep. Momentum. Self-respect.</p>
      <p>You already felt that on ScrollTax. Now this is the part where you actually fix it.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>What this reset does</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li>breaks the automatic urge to open scrolling apps</li>
        <li>helps you identify what triggers the habit</li>
        <li>gives you replacements so you do not fall right back in</li>
        <li>helps you take control without becoming extreme or unrealistic</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>What happens if you do nothing</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>You already know the pattern:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>“just 10 minutes” turns into an hour</li>
        <li>you feel worse after, not better</li>
        <li>you tell yourself tomorrow will be different</li>
        <li>nothing changes</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="highlight">Most people stay stuck in that loop for years.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>What you get</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Day 1:</strong> remove friction killers and make scrolling harder</li>
        <li><strong>Day 2:</strong> identify your real trigger: boredom, stress, fatigue, avoidance</li>
        <li><strong>Day 3:</strong> replace scrolling with fast, low-effort alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Day 4:</strong> create one protected no-scroll zone in your day</li>
        <li><strong>Day 5:</strong> measure the real cost so your brain stops minimizing it</li>
        <li><strong>Day 6:</strong> build a shutoff ritual that actually sticks</li>
        <li><strong>Day 7:</strong> lock in one identity shift so you stop defaulting back</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Why this works</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>Because this is not based on guilt alone.</p>
      <p>It is based on <strong>friction, replacement, awareness, and control</strong>.</p>
      <p>That is what actually changes behavior.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="price-box section-space">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Get the full ScrollTax Reset</h2>
      <p>One simple system. No fluff. No self-help nonsense. Just a practical reset that helps you get control back.</p>

      <div class="price">€9</div>

      <a href="#" class="button">Get the full reset now</a>

      <p class="small">Replace this link with your Stripe or Gumroad checkout link.</p>
      <p class="small">One-time payment.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card section-space">
      <p><strong>Read this carefully:</strong></p>
      <p>You do not have a motivation problem.</p>
      <p>You have a loop.</p>
      <p>The longer you stay in it, the more normal it feels.</p>
      <p class="warning">That is exactly why most people never fix it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
